content.description: Yellow Pages is essentially a direct version of the problem On a Wing and a Prayer. Sit start at center of steep wall with left hand on a big sloper and right hand in the crack/seam. Move up to the big ledge, and top out.
content.location: This ascends the center of the wall.

climbs.name: On a Wing and a Prayer

content.description: Sit start matched on low feature on the far left side of the block. Move right across the steep wall into the crack/seam in the middle of the wall, then head straight up, and top out.
content.location: Start on the far left matched on a low feature as for the problem Diamond in the Rough.

content.description: Sit start at far right side of the steep boulder using two small crimps. Move left and match on a sloper and then a flake. Move into the crack/seam, and set up for a tough exit moves to a pair of crimps up high. You get full value if you stay right of the crack/seam during the topout.
content.location: This ascends the far right end of the block.

content.description: Sit start matched on a low feature, and move up and left through the steep arete to a mantle and slab finish. One of the cruxes is staying clear of the rock that's on the nearby wall which juts out.
content.location: This ascends the far left side of the boulder.

content.description: Overpass Boulder is one steep block built into the hillside.
